The paper deals with the problem of frequent episode mining, which is a subfield of data mining and database systems (cs.DB). The proposed method involves using a partition model to filter out free-rider episodes, which is a common problem in pattern mining and can be addressed using machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques (cs.AI). The paper also involves statistical modeling and hypothesis testing to compare observed and expected support values, which are common techniques in machine learning and statistical analysis (cs.LG). The experiments involve using synthetic and real-world datasets, which are commonly used in data science and machine learning research (cs.DS). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of pattern mining and discovering interesting patterns, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR).
